item.title: Can you make your computer untraceable?
item.dc:creator: @Explisionist Explisionist
item.description:
@Explisionist wrote:

[quote=“Davidi2, post:8, topic:312406”][quote author=Explisionist link=topic=408807.msg3017685#msg3017685 date=1257310806]
Google Chrome allows you to use the Incognito window, which basically doesn’t use cookies or save your ip address.

[code]in·cog·ni·to (nkg-nt, n-kgn-t)
adv. & adj.
With one’s identity disguised or concealed.
n. pl. in·cog·ni·tos

  1. One whose identity is disguised or concealed.
  2. The condition of having a disguised or concealed identity.[/code]
    [/quote]
    That’s doesnt mean they can’t track you if you visit their website…[/quote]

Your ip address shows back as unavailable they cannot search it.
